article.headline: Sacramento St. 72, William Jessup 54
article.story: SACRAMENTO, Calif. (AP) -- Loren Leath had 22 points and five rebounds and Vinnie McGhee added eight points and 14 assists to lead Sacramento State over William Jessup 72-54 on Tuesday night. Justin Williams added 12 points and eight rebounds and Jason Davis scored 11 points and grabbed six rebounds for the Hornets (2-6). Matt Cassell had 11 points and Max Botner and Lucas Birchard added 10 points each for the Warriors (5-5). The struggling Hornets had a 13-point lead in the second half until the NAIA school came back to trim the margin on a free throw by Torben Seikowsky at the 4:13 mark to make the score 55-51. Sac State used a 17-3 run, defense and clock management to hold on for the victory. The Hornets missed their first six shots, but recovered to lead 33-21 on a free throw by Jason Davis with 3:11 left in the first half. Sac State led 38-29 at halftime.
